  "flow": "FLOW",
  "howDoIGetStarted": "How do I get started with Flow?",
  "howDoIGetStartedAnswer": "After creating your account, you'll go through a quick onboarding process where you'll set your goals, preferences, and basic information. Once complete, you can start logging meals, workouts, and track your progress on the dashboard.",
  "howDoISetTargets": "How do I set my daily calorie and nutrient targets?",
  "howDoISetTargetsAnswer": "Your targets are automatically calculated based on your profile information (age, weight, height, activity level, and goals). You can adjust these in your Profile settings at any time.",
  "whatAreCoins": "What are coins and how do I earn them?",
  "whatAreCoinsAnswer": "Coins are Flow's reward currency. You earn coins by completing daily activities like logging meals, completing workouts, and participating in challenges. Use coins to unlock premium features and rewards.",
  "howDoILogMeal": "How do I log a meal?",
  "howDoILogMealAnswer": "Tap the \"+\" button on your dashboard, select a meal type (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, or Snack), then search for foods, scan a barcode, take a photo, or use voice input. You can also add custom foods with your own nutritional information.",
  "canILogMealsPhotos": "Can I log meals using photos?",
  "canILogMealsPhotosAnswer": "Yes! Flow uses advanced image recognition to identify foods from photos. Simply take a photo of your meal, and Flow will recognize the foods and their estimated portions. You can then adjust quantities and add them to your log.",
  "howDoesVoiceInputWork": "How does voice input work?",
  "howDoesVoiceInputWorkAnswer": "Tap the microphone icon when adding a meal, speak what you're eating (e.g., \"chicken breast with rice\"), and Flow will recognize the foods and help you log them quickly.",
  "whatIfFoodNotInDatabase": "What if a food isn't in the database?",
  "whatIfFoodNotInDatabaseAnswer": "You can create custom foods by entering the nutritional information manually. These custom foods will be saved to your account and appear in your recent foods list for easy access.",
  "howAccurateNutritionTracking": "How accurate is the nutrition tracking?",
  "howAccurateNutritionTrackingAnswer": "Flow uses comprehensive nutrition databases and AI recognition to provide accurate nutritional information. However, portion sizes from photos are estimates - you can always adjust quantities to match your actual serving size.",
  "howDoILogWorkout": "How do I log a workout?",
  "howDoILogWorkoutAnswer": "Go to the Workouts section, tap \"Log Workout\", select an exercise from the database or create a custom one, enter sets, reps, and weight, then save. The calories burned will be automatically calculated and added to your daily totals.",
  "canICreateWorkoutPlans": "Can I create my own workout plans?",
  "canICreateWorkoutPlansAnswer": "Yes! You can create custom workout plans in the Programs section. Add exercises, set schedules, and track your progress over time.",
  "howAreCaloriesBurnedCalculated": "How are calories burned calculated?",
  "howAreCaloriesBurnedCalculatedAnswer": "Calories burned are calculated based on the exercise type, duration, intensity, and your personal profile information (weight, age, etc.).",
  "howDoIFindRecipes": "How do I find recipes?",
  "howDoIFindRecipesAnswer": "Go to the Recipes section to browse our collection of healthy recipes. You can filter by meal type, cuisine, dietary preferences, and search by ingredients or tags.",
  "canICreateRecipes": "Can I create my own recipes?",
  "canICreateRecipesAnswer": "Absolutely! Tap \"Create Recipe\" to add your own custom recipes. Enter ingredients, instructions, nutritional information per serving, and upload a photo. Your recipes will be saved to your account.",
  "howDoIAddRecipeToMealLog": "How do I add a recipe to my meal log?",
  "howDoIAddRecipeToMealLogAnswer": "When viewing a recipe, select your meal type and tap \"Add as Meal\". Flow will calculate the nutritional values based on the number of servings you consumed.",
  "whatAreFlowChallenges": "What are Flow Challenges?",
  "whatAreFlowChallengesAnswer": "Flow Challenges are community-driven goals that help you stay motivated. Join challenges like \"Drink 2L Water Daily\" or \"Complete 10 Workouts This Month\" to earn rewards and compete with others.",
  "howDoIJoinChallenge": "How do I join a challenge?",
  "howDoIJoinChallengeAnswer": "Go to the Challenges section, browse available challenges, and tap \"Join Now\" on any challenge that interests you. Your progress will be automatically tracked based on your logged activities.",
  "howIsChallengeProgressCalculated": "How is my challenge progress calculated?",
  "howIsChallengeProgressCalculatedAnswer": "Progress is automatically calculated from your logged meals, workouts, and activities. For example, if you join a protein challenge, your daily protein intake is tracked from your meal logs.",
  "whatIsVitalityBreakdown": "What is Vitality Breakdown?",
  "whatIsVitalityBreakdownAnswer": "Vitality Breakdown is your comprehensive nutrient monitoring hub. It shows all vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and specialized nutrients you've consumed, compared to recommended daily allowances (RDA).",
  "whatIsVitalityShield": "What is Vitality Shield?",
  "whatIsVitalityShieldAnswer": "Vitality Shield provides critical alerts for nutrient deficiencies (e.g., low calcium for multiple days) and warnings for excessive intake (high sodium, sugar, caffeine). It helps you maintain optimal nutrition balance.",
  "howDoIViewNutrientTrends": "How do I view my nutrient trends?",
  "howDoIViewNutrientTrendsAnswer": "Tap on any nutrient in Vitality Breakdown to see a weekly trend graph showing your intake over the last 7 days. You can share these charts with others.",
  "canIViewPastDaysNutrition": "Can I view past days' nutrition data?",
  "canIViewPastDaysNutritionAnswer": "Yes! Use the date picker in Vitality Breakdown to view any previous day's nutritional data and see how your intake has changed over time.",
  "whatIsAICoach": "What is the AI Coach?",
  "whatIsAICoachAnswer": "The AI Coach provides personalized nutrition and fitness advice based on your goals, logged data, and progress. Ask questions, get meal suggestions, and receive guidance tailored to your journey.",
  "howDoesFoodRecognitionWork": "How does food recognition work?",
  "howDoesFoodRecognitionWorkAnswer": "Flow uses advanced image recognition technology to identify foods from photos. The system recognizes multiple foods in a single image and estimates portion sizes to help you log meals quickly.",
  "isMyDataUsedToTrainAI": "Is my data used to train AI models?",
  "isMyDataUsedToTrainAIAnswer": "Your personal data is private and secure. We use aggregated, anonymized data to improve our services, but your individual information is never shared or used without your consent.",
  "howDoIExportData": "How do I export my data?",
  "howDoIExportDataAnswer": "Go to Export Data in the menu. You can export your nutrition data as CSV or JSON files, or generate a PDF report. Select your date range and choose your preferred format.",
  "canIDeleteAccount": "Can I delete my account?",
  "canIDeleteAccountAnswer": "Yes, you can delete your account from your Profile settings. This will permanently remove all your data. Please contact support if you need assistance.",
  "howDoIChangePassword": "How do I change my password?",
  "howDoIChangePasswordAnswer": "Go to your Profile, then Settings, and select \"Change Password\". You'll receive an email with instructions to reset your password.",
  "isMyDataSecure": "Is my data secure?",
  "isMyDataSecureAnswer": "Absolutely. We use industry-standard encryption and security measures to protect your data. Your information is stored securely and never shared with third parties without your explicit consent.",
